# Environment template for the Lumecon site.
# Copy to .env (gitignored) for local dev, or set these in the CI/
# deploy environment for production builds.
#
# Astro inlines any var prefixed with PUBLIC_ at build time so it's
# readable from the client bundle. Anything that shouldn't be public
# (e.g., a server-side API key) must NOT be prefixed PUBLIC_ — keep
# it on the backend or in a build-time-only secret.

# ---- Backend (AWS) ----
# Base URL of the Lumecon application API (AWS API Gateway / custom
# domain). Leave unset on the marketing-only branch — src/lib/api.ts
# returns { ok: false, reason: 'api-unconfigured' } and components
# fall back to their no-API behaviour (e.g., mailto: contact form,
# local Cedar classifier).
#
# Example production value:
#   PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.lumecon.ai
PUBLIC_API_URL=

# ---- Observability (Datadog RUM) ----
# All five must be set for the SDK to initialize; if any is missing,
# every track*() call is a no-op. Get the application id + client
# token from the Datadog RUM application setup page; SITE is your
# Datadog region (datadoghq.com / datadoghq.eu / us3.datadoghq.com /
# etc.); SERVICE is the logical service name; ENV separates
# production from staging/preview data.
#
# Wire-up: install @datadog/browser-rum, uncomment the init block
# in src/lib/observability.ts, and extend BaseLayout.astro's CSP
# `connect-src` to include https://*.{PUBLIC_DATADOG_SITE}.
PUBLIC_DATADOG_APPLICATION_ID=
PUBLIC_DATADOG_CLIENT_TOKEN=
PUBLIC_DATADOG_SITE=
PUBLIC_DATADOG_SERVICE=
PUBLIC_DATADOG_ENV=
